Description: Opensource TERSE/AMATERSE/TRSMAIN compatible compressor/decomp

OpenTerse is a reimplementation of the z/OS TERSE data
compression format (PACK, SPACK and their common inverse, UNPACK).

This package installs the OPNTERSE load module into SYS2.LINKLIB and
adds TRSMAIN and AMATERSE as aliases for it, so any existing JCL that
invokes PGM=TRSMAIN or PGM=AMATERSE runs OPNTERSE unmodified -- it
mimics their PARM='PACK'|'SPACK'|'UNPACK' and SYSUT1/SYSUT2/SYSPRINT
(and TRSMAIN's INFILE/OUTFILE) calling convention.

Example, unchanged from existing TRSMAIN/AMATERSE JCL:

  //SPACK    EXEC PGM=TRSMAIN,PARM='SPACK'
  //SYSUT1   DD DSN=IBMUSER.SOURCE.DATA,DISP=SHR
  //SYSUT2   DD DSN=IBMUSER.SOURCE.SPACK,DISP=(NEW,CATLG,DELETE),...
  //SYSPRINT DD SYSOUT=*
